lemma dense_interval: assumes "finite L" "finite U" "l \<in> L" "u \<in> U" "l < x" "x < u" "P(x::real)" and dense: "\<And>y l u. \<lbrakk> \<forall>y\<in>{l<..<x}. y \<notin> L; \<forall>y\<in>{x<..<u}. y \<notin> U; l<x;x<u; l<y;y<u \<rbrakk> \<Longrightarrow> P y" shows "\<exists>l\<in>L.\<exists>u\<in>U. l<u \<and> (\<forall>y. l<y \<and> y<u \<longrightarrow> P y)"
